-- Ukraine Central Bank's Lenders Stress Test `Credit Positive,' Moody's Says
-- Daryna Krasnolutska
-- 2010-07-12T10:49:47Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-07-12/ukraine-central-bank-s-lenders-stress-test-credit-positive-moody-s-says.html

          
          
             Moody’s Investors Service said that
the Ukrainain central bank’s recommendation for commercial banks
to boost their capital by a combined 40 billion hryvnia ($5
billion) following a stress test is “credit positive.”  
 Moody’s, in a statement today, also said the recommendation
will improve the capitalization of the banking system in Ukraine
and increase their ability to absorb credit losses.  
 The National Bank of Ukraine on July 2 published the
results of its stress test, which affect 61 banks.  
